<header class="hero">
    {{> logo}}

    <h1 class="site-title">Norr</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Transport agnostic post-quantum encrypted protocol for decentralized communication</p>

    <nav class="nav">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
    </nav>
</header>

<main>
    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">What is Norr?</h2>
        <p>Norr is a communication protocol designed for resilient, decentralized messaging. It works across any transport layer - from the internet to radio waves - and uses post-quantum encryption to ensure your messages stay private, even against future threats.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Key Features</h2>
        <div class="features">
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <div class="feature-title">Transport Agnostic</div>
                    <p class="feature-description">Works over TCP/IP, LoRa, packet radio, or any other transport. Your communication isn't tied to infrastructure that might fail.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <div class="feature-title">Post-Quantum Encryption</div>
                    <p class="feature-description">Uses modern cryptographic algorithms designed to withstand attacks from quantum computers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <div class="feature-title">Decentralized</div>
                    <p class="feature-description">No central servers required. Messages can hop through any available node to reach their destination.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
                <div class="feature-content">
                    <div class="feature-title">Low Bandwidth</div>
                    <p class="feature-description">Optimized for constrained environments. Send messages even over the slowest connections.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Status</h2>
        <p>Norr is currently in active development. The protocol specification is being refined and reference implementations are being built.</p>
    </section>
</main>

<footer class="footer">
    <p class="footer-text">{{footer}}</p>
    <p class="footer-location">{{location}}</p>

    <div class="theme-toggle">
        <span class="theme-toggle-label">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/><line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="3"/><line x1="12" y1="21" x2="12" y2="23"/><line x1="4.22" y1="4.22" x2="5.64" y2="5.64"/><line x1="18.36" y1="18.36" x2="19.78" y2="19.78"/><line x1="1" y1="12" x2="3" y2="12"/><line x1="21" y1="12" x2="23" y2="12"/><line x1="4.22" y1="19.78" x2="5.64" y2="18.36"/><line x1="18.36" y1="5.64" x2="19.78" y2="4.22"/></svg>
        </span>
        <label class="theme-switch">
            <input type="checkbox" id="theme-toggle-input" aria-label="Toggle dark mode">
            <span class="theme-switch-track"></span>
        </label>
        <span class="theme-toggle-label">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 12.79A9 9 0 1 1 11.21 3 7 7 0 0 0 21 12.79z"/></svg>
        </span>
